<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<h3>What This Policy Covers</h3>
<br />
<p>Chiive takes your privacy seriously.  This privacy policy (“the Policy”) governs how the Chiive service and website (collectively, the “Service”), found at www.chiive.com, collect and use information about you.  This Policy does not cover information that you provide to, or that is gathered by, companies that Chiive does not own or control, or to individuals that Chiive does not employ.  By registering for and using Chiive, you agree to the terms of the Policy. </p><br />

<h3>The Information We Collect and How We Use It </h3>
<br />

<p><u>Personal information you provide to us</u></p>
<p><br />
Personal information is information about you that identifies you personally, such as your name, address, email address, etc.  When you register for the Chiive service, we request your name, email address and location information.  You may also choose to provide us with additional information, such as age, gender, profile photograph, family, relationships, activities, interests, etc.  We use this information to allow you to invite friends to connect with you using Chiive, interact with other users of Chiive, improve Chiive’s content, customize the advertising and content you see, and communicate with you about the Chiive service.  By using the Service, you consent to Chiive’s use of your personal information for these purposes. </p>
<br />

<p><u>Information we collect automatically</u></p>
<p><br />
Chiive automatically collects and stores certain nonpersonal information when you interact with the Service.  Examples of nonpersonal information that Chiive collects include the identity of your web browser, the type of operating system you use, your IP address, Chiive cookie information and the domain name of your Internet service provider.  Chiive also automatically collects information about site traffic, such as the number and frequency of visits to the site, the locations of users visiting the site, and clickstream data (such as the pages visited and time spent at each page)</p>
<br />
<p>Chiive aggregates this nonpersonal information to help us understand how our subscribers use the Site.  We use this aggregated information to evaluate site use, assess and improve site performance, and improve the content of the Site.  We do not combine this information with personal information to tell us who you are or what your contact information is. </p>
<p>Chiive also automatically collects information about your location in real time to help you find events created by your Chiive connections, and to help your Chiive connections find your events.  Photos are tagged with location permanently. Chiive does not track the user’s movements when not actively contributing content to the site. Chiive does, however, track and analyze location information on an aggregated basis, as described above, to assist us in analyzing subscribers’ needs and improving the Chiive service.  By using the Service, you consent to Chiive’s use of your nonpersonal information for these purposes. </p>
<br />
<p><u>Cookies</u></p>
<br />
<p>A cookie is a small text file that Chiive places on your computer’s hard drive which enable Chiive to recognize your computer.  Chiive’s cookies do not collect personal information. </p>
<p>Chiive’s advertising partners may place cookies on your hard drives to assist them in compiling information about you and delivering targeted advertising to you.  This Policy does not cover the use of cookies by advertisers. </p>
<p>Most browsers allow you to prevent cookies from being placed on your hard drive.  You can remove or block cookies using this feature in your browser, but doing so may prevent you from using some of Chiive’s features. </p>
<br />
<p><u>Children</u></p>
<br />
<p>Chiive does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. </p>


